 4.  Terminology

    This section defines terminology and abbreviations used in this
-   document.  It extends the terminology of [RFC8376].
+   document.  It extends the terminology of [RFC8376] and incorporates the
+   core terms from the SCHC Architecture [draft-ietf-schc-architecture-06].

    The SCHC acronym is pronounced like "sheek" in English (or "chic" in
    French).  Therefore, this document writes "a SCHC Packet" instead of
    "an SCHC Packet".

    App:     LPWAN Application Server, as defined by [RFC8376].  It runs
             an application sending/receiving packets to/from the Dev.

    AppIID:  Application Interface Identifier.  The IID that identifies
             the App interface.

    Compression Residue:  The bits that remain to be sent (beyond the
             RuleID itself) after applying the SCHC compression.

-   Context:  A set of Rules used to compress/decompress headers, or to
-            fragment/reassemble a packet.
+   Context:  Operational information shared between two or more Instances
+            in a Domain, comprising a Set of Rules (SoR) and optional metadata
+            (such as Parser and Data Model descriptors).

    Dev:     Device, as defined by [RFC8376].

    DevIID:  Device Interface Identifier.  The IID that identifies the
             Dev interface.

+   Discriminator: An information element (e.g., lower-layer device ID,
+            DevEUI, or UDP port) used by a Dispatcher to route SCHC Datagrams
+            to the appropriate SCHC Instance.

+   Dispatcher: A logical component of a SCHC Endpoint that routes incoming
+            SCHC Datagrams to the appropriate SCHC Instance based on defined
+            admission rules and Discriminators.
+
+   Domain:  A logical grouping of SCHC Instances that share a common set
+            of Contexts for SCHC operations.

+   Endpoint: A logical entity providing SCHC functionality by hosting one
+            or more SCHC Instances.

    Downlink:  From the App to the Dev.

+   Instance: A logical component of a SCHC Endpoint that executes the actual
+            SCHC operations (C/D and F/R) using its assigned Context and
+            Instance Configuration.

    L2:      Layer 2.  The immediate lower layer that SCHC interfaces
             with, for example an underlying LPWAN technology.

    L2 Word:  This is the minimum subdivision of payload data that the L2
             will carry.

    Padding:  Extra bits that may be appended by SCHC to a data unit that
             it passes down to L2 for transmission.

    Profile:  SCHC offers variations in the way it is operated, with a
             number of parameters listed in Appendix D.  A Profile
             indicates a particular setting of all these parameters.

    Rule:    Part of the Context that describes how a packet is
             compressed/decompressed or fragmented/reassembled, identified
             by a RuleID.

    RuleID:  Rule Identifier.  An identifier for a Rule within a Context.

    SCHC:    Static Context Header Compression and fragmentation (SCHC),
             a generic framework.

    SCHC C/D:  SCHC Compressor/Decompressor function executed within a
             SCHC Instance to achieve header compression/decompression.

    SCHC F/R:  SCHC Fragmenter/Reassembler function executed within a
             SCHC Instance to achieve fragmentation/reassembly of SCHC Packets.

    SCHC Packet:  A packet whose header has been compressed by SCHC C/D.

+   Session: A communication session between two or more SCHC Instances that
+            share a common Context.

+   Set of Rules (SoR): The collection of C/D, F/R, and no-compression Rules
+            available in a Context.

+   Set of Variables (SoV): Runtime parameters and session variables (such as
+            fragmentation timers, retransmission counters, and bitmaps) that
+            change during SCHC operation.

